		"description": "<p>At 3rd level, you learn a variety of techniques to draw attention to yourself in a fight. You gain proficiency with your choice of the Performance skill or the Intimidation skill.</p>\n<p>You become proficient with the Cutting Omen combat tradition.</p>\n<p>You also learn to quickly decorate your armor and weapons to maximum effect. You may spend 10 minutes to grant the flamboyant property to weapons you wield.</p>\n<p>Finally, choose five multiclass spells associated with the fighter class and add them to your fighter spells known. They do not count against your total spells known.</p>",
